# Cursor Pointer on Clickable Elements

All interactive/clickable elements must have `cursor: pointer` styling.

## Rules

- Every `<button>` element must include `cursor-pointer` (Tailwind) or `style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }}`.
- Every element with an `onClick` handler must include `cursor-pointer` or `style={{ cursor: 'pointer' }}`.
- This applies to `<div>`, `<span>`, `<a>`, `<li>`, or any other element that has `onClick`.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — missing cursor pointer
<button onClick={handleClick}>Submit</button>
<div onClick={toggleMenu}>Menu</div>

// ✅ GOOD — cursor pointer applied
<button className="cursor-pointer" onClick={handleClick}>Submit</button>
<div className="cursor-pointer" onClick={toggleMenu}>Menu</div>
```
